                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13103206" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 13 Sep 2011 00:13:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You can workaround this by explicitly disabling it in the config:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;auto_bootstrap: false&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But imo, when a token is specified we should automatically assume there is no need to bootstrap.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103213" author="tjake" created="Tue, 13 Sep 2011 00:27:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The fact the option is missing from the config will make it hard for users to fix without pulling some hair out.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103307" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 13 Sep 2011 03:50:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is your single node not a seed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103614" author="tjake" created="Tue, 13 Sep 2011 13:13:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I left the listen address blank.  and the seed is 127.0.0.1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103733" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 13 Sep 2011 16:27:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I could be wrong, but I think that was is happening here is that leaving it blank will resolve to the machine address (i.e, not the loopback ip), and thus the node doesn&apos;t recognize itself as a seed. In a way, it&apos;s a configuration error, listen_address should be 127.0.0.1. Not sure we can really improve that error message, but maybe we can improve the comments in the yaml.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103766" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 13 Sep 2011 17:07:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to explain the problem and how to solve it in the exception message.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13103773" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 13 Sep 2011 17:14:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103797" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 13 Sep 2011 17:30:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
